<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include("partials/head", {
    pageTitle: "Web Development Process"
  }) %>

  <body>
    <%- include("partials/nav") %>

    <main>
      <section class="page-title">
        <p class="eyebrow">From idea to website</p>
        <h1>Web Development Process</h1>

        <p>
          Following an organized process helps developers create
          websites that are easier to use and maintain.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="two-column">
        <article>
          <h2>Steps in Web Development</h2>

          <p>
            Before coding, developers should understand the purpose
            of the website and who will use it.
          </p>

          <ol class="process-list">
            <li>Plan the website goal and content.</li>
            <li>Create a layout or wireframe.</li>
            <li>Write HTML for the structure.</li>
            <li>Use CSS to style the page.</li>
            <li>Test links, images, and layout.</li>
            <li>Validate the HTML code.</li>
            <li>Publish the website online.</li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="/img/process.jpg"
            alt="Web development process"
          >
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section class="info-box">
        <h2>Why the Process Matters</h2>

        <p>
          Following a process saves time and reduces mistakes. It
          also helps developers make websites that are easier to
          update later.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <%- include("partials/footer") %>
  </body>
</html>